For those who are having problem while installing tensorflow and keras:

Step #1:
Open anaconda prompt and run as administrator.

Step #2:
Write following commands ('tensorflow' is the name of the environment, you can change it to anything)

>conda create -n tensorflow python=3.6 anaconda
>activate tensorflow

Step#3:
>conda install spyder (optional)

after that use thsese commands (prompt Y to install the following):

>conda install tensorflow
>conda install keras

Step #4:
You will be needing these packages

>pip install matplotlib
>pip install pandas
>pip install sklearn

Step#5:
upgrade all packages by this command:

>conda upgrade â€“all

Now you are ready to go!!!

See after opening anaconda navigator>environments there will be new environment named "tensorflow" will be installed.
